###Cloudwatch Sythetics:-

 CloudWatch Synthetics to create canaries, configurable scripts that run on a schedule,
 to monitor your endpoints and APIs. Canaries follow the same routes and perform the same actions as a customer, 
 which makes it possible for you to continually verify your customer experience even when you don't have any customer
 traffic on your applications. By using canaries, you can discover issues before your customers do

 For the testing Simple web-portal, i was made use of https://www.amazon.com

 Open the cloudwatch portal 
 In the Navigation pane under the synthetics ,select Synthetics
 select create canary-->"use Blueprint"--->"heatBeatMonitoring"
 Enter the name of canary
 Application or endpoints URL as www.amazon.com 
 Rest leave it default options. Note there is option to createAlarm also.
 Hit Create Canary-- This will take around 5 to 10 minutes
 cananry will hit this website every 5 minute check if its available or not.
 It will even check the insiide api calls of amazon and response time
 
 You will home page of www.amzon.com getting refreshed every 5 min, same one customer seems.
 
